# Admin editor sheets (add / edit forms)

Treat this as **one checklist** whenever you add or change a **form** in `*sheet*.tsx` (Fault management, Administration, File management, etc.).

## Layout

- **No inner form container:** do not wrap the form in **`Card` / `CardContent`**, a **‚ÄúConfiguration‚Äù** titled panel, or any extra **bordered** box inside `SheetContent`. Header + padded scroll body + footer are enough.

## Spacing (required ‚Äî same as full-page admin forms)

- **`FieldGroup`** wraps the vertical stack of fields; **`Field`** + **`FieldLabel`** + control per field. This is **not optional** for sheet bodies: it encodes label‚Üícontrol **`gap-4`** and between-field **`gap-8`** via `field.tsx`.
- **Do not** use **`Label` + `space-y-2` / `space-y-4`** (or `mt-*` hacks) for stacked fields in sheets ‚Äî that bypasses the design system and will look wrong.
- **Checkbox / radio beside text:** **`gap-3`** between control and label; see **`form-field-spacing.mdc`**.

## Footer

- **`SheetFooter`**: Cancel (outline) + primary save, unless the screen needs a left action (e.g. ‚ÄúApply to all‚Äù).

## References

- Good examples: **`custom-event-sheet.tsx`**, **`fault-event-edit-sheet.tsx`**.
- Spacing spec: **`form-field-spacing.mdc`**.
- Legacy contrast: **`add-domain-sheet.tsx`**, **`add-radio-node-sheet.tsx`** still use an inner `Card` ‚Äî **new or touched** admin form sheets should follow this rule instead.
